# Hinomori Roblox Luau Rules

- Roblox Luau project using Rojo 7.7 and Wally packages.
- Co-located services live in `src/services/<Name>/` with Client, Server, Shared modules.
- Server modules sync to `ServerScriptService.Services`; client/shared sync to `ReplicatedStorage.Shared.Services`.
- Startup scripts: `src/startup/Server.server.luau`, `src/startup/Client.client.luau`.
- Shared utilities: `src/modules/` (Core, Game, Math, Platform).
- UI: `src/ui/` - `init.luau` mounts the persistent HUD; client services mount feature menus. No monolithic UIController.
- Player data: `src/shared/Data.luau` via DataServiceTyped; mutate only through DataService on server.
- Networking: Networker only; whitelist client-callable methods explicitly on each service server.
- Never trust client for locker state, notes, hand-offs, arcade scores, or inventory.
- Prefer plain Luau modules over Knit/Roact/Fusion unless explicitly requested.
- Do not invent Roblox APIs.
- Map geometry stays in Studio; do not put world building logic in repo scripts unless requested.
- Tag new systems with implementation status from AGENTS.md (Implemented / Prototype / Planned).
- Read `AGENTS.md` and `docs/CURRENT_STATE.md` before editing. The repository is self-contained; do not require the owner's private llm-wiki.
- Use the shared Team Create place as world truth. The tracked `rural.rbxl` is a legacy snapshot.
- Missing world objects must fail locally with a warning, not break UI/service startup.
